HEADWORD: Polygamia
<hw>Pol`y*ga"mi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Polygamous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
Linn⟦ae⟧an class of plants, characterized by having both hermaphrodite
and unisexual flowers on the same plant.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A name
given by Linn⟦ae⟧us to file orders of plants having syngenesious
flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

